item.text: The fountain is radiant and the water is fresh. After many treks in the woods, quenching your thirst is welcome.

bio.name: Ever burning flame II
bio.description: This ever burning flame cannot be extinguished by normal means. You think water from the World Sea, also known as Prime Water, might do the trick.

bio.name: Out of flames
bio.description: The burning pillar kindly asks you to bring it a Scroll of Fire Ball, so that it may empower its flame. It promises you riches if you do so.

bio.name: Kill Tamrahk
bio.description:
Tamrahk is thought to be performing a demonic ritual in order to summon the Wicked One. Reports suggests that the ritual is being performed on an island not too far from here.

Kill this foul demon before it is too late.

bio.name: The waters shall part
bio.description: The wanderer bids you you to put out the ever burning flames on an island to the north west. He promises you that he will reveal a path he thinks might aid you in your quest.

bio.name: Door of Phaal
bio.description: The door is ancient. It will only open while you carry a Phaal Glyph.

bio.name: A source of water
bio.description: Some pesky Breakers have blocked the path to a nearby fountain. This curious statue informs you that it wants this fountain to be available for all travelers who pass through this land, as it give much needed rehydration.
